FBIS4-52185 "dreas089_c_94006" FBIS-EAS-94-089 Daily Report 7 May 1994 North Korea Radio Reports Collision of U.S Planes in South Radio Reports Collision of U.S Planes in South SK0805061594 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean 2217 GMT 7 May 94 SK0805061594 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network in Korean 2217 GMT 7 May 94 Korean BFN [Text] According to a radio report from Seoul, two U.S. Army fighter planes, which were running amok in a war exercise, collided in the skies above the sea southwest of Sosan, South Chungchong Province on 6 May. The fighter planes were broken into pieces and bits and one pilot was missing due to the aerial collision. The U.S. imperialist aggressive forces are frequently bringing about such an accident while bustling about in the war exercise to invade the North.
